data.title: Regent Benzole Petrol advert, 1955
data.meta_description: Benzole addative petrol is more usually associated with National Benzole (or British Benzole) - however it was also used by other petrol brands including Regent. Regent was a brand associated with Texaco. Benzole was phased out following a realisation that it was not a nice substance to go around burning no matter how much it improved car engine performance - it was largely superseded by tetraethyl lead, now recognised as a major pollutant itself.
